$Id: README 651 2005-05-11 03:36:01Z phf $

A basic single-pass compiler for a MINImalistic programming language

Peter Froehlich <phf@acm.org>
http://www.factorial.com/forward/phf/work/

The programming language Mini was designed by Fridtjof Siebert, see
the KUDOS file. The language is unchanged, all the original example
programs work (modulo machine restrictions that is). :-)

This version is written in Python and generates MIPS code for the
SPIM simulator, MMIX code, LC-3 code, PowerPC code for Mac OS X,
or Intel 80386 code for Linux.

mini.tex
mini.pdf
  Loose translation of Fridtjof's Mini.LiesMich file
  Added commentary and tutorial on this implementation

buffer.py
generator.py
i386.py
lc3.py
mini.py
